<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1896-10-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1896-10-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="598" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d598">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Taylor</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">San
                                        Sebastian</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-10-10"><hi rend="italic">October 10,
                                1896</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Minister for foreign affairs promises relief in every ease of contract
                            made before decree prohibiting shipment. Will also telegraph Cuba urging
                            noninterference in all cases where it is clear that contract was made
                            before decree.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Taylor</hi>.</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>